and hence the language is known only in written form. There must be
sufficient text to allow the Adept to achieve the requisite rank.
(Players should record the languages and rank they know using this
talent, and also those that they have failed to master.)

An Adept may increase Rank with a dead language that he has mastered
by spending one week per Rank practising the language (at no
Experience cost) until he knows it at the same Rank as his Rank with
this talent. If he wishes to gain Rank with a dead language which is
greater than his Rank with this talent, he must follow the normal
procedure to gain Rank with a language as described in 49 and 87 (in
the DragonQuest rules).  This talent's Experience Multiple is 150.
d210 17
a226 14
Any Adept of this College has a 25\% chance  (+3 / Rank)  of  being
able to break any code or  cipher  created  by  an  Adept  of  this
college using T-4 if he studies it for  12  hours  (-l / Rank,+l / Rank
of the Adept who created the code  or  cipher  with  T-4  )  .  The
Adept's chances of breaking such a cipher  or  code  are  decreased
by 3 for every Rank the Adept who created the code  or  cipher  had
with T-4 (Create Codes and Ciphers)  of  this  College.  The  Adept
must concentrate on breaking this code or cipher  for  an  unbroken
period of time equal  to  that  necessary  to  break  the  code  or
cipher before a D100 roll can be made  (by  the  GM)  to  determine
his success. The Adept's rank in  breaking  non-magical  codes  and
ciphers is equal to his rank in this talent  (T-1).  This  talent's
Experience Multiple is 150.

